cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is about building an automatic speech recognition system for Somali, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also mentions using neural architectures, which falls under cs.SD (Sound). Additionally, the paper discusses data augmentation techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also involves training models and evaluating performance, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of keyword spotting systems for humanitarian relief programs, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
